message.content:
A Polistes instabilis is a species of paper wasp commonly found in North America. 
It has a slender body with long antennae and characteristic yellow and black markings on its head and thorax. 
The abdomen is primarily dark with some yellow stripes. 
The wings are thin and transparent. 
Paper wasps like Polistes instabilis are often found building nests on trees or on man-made structures. 
They are important pollinators but can also sting when threatened. 
Polistes instabilis is often observed in gardens and natural habitats, making it a familiar sight to many people.
